{"word":"H2111 - זוּעַ - zûwaʻ - zoo'-ah - Move","slug":"H2111","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">זוּעַ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>zûwaʻ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>zoo'-ah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Move"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D6;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05E2; - zu&#x0302;a&#x201B;</b> - <i>zoo'-ah</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>shake</i> off, that is, (figuratively) to <i>agitate</i> (as with fear): - move, tremble, vex."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2113\">H2113</a>, <a href=\"#/H2127\">H2127</a>, <a href=\"#/H2189\">H2189</a>"}]}